The paper deals with graph theory and metric spaces, which are topics covered in several arXiv CS sub-categories. However, the focus on chordal graphs and real trees suggests that the paper is most likely to be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of metric spaces and distance drawings also suggests a possible classification under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of intersection models and the study of graph properties suggest a possible classification under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
